The paper deals with constructing a sparse spanning subgraph, which is a fundamental problem in graph theory. The algorithm is designed for the Centralized Local model, which is a distributed computing model. Therefore, cs.DS (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves approximation algorithms and graph theory, which suggests cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) as likely sub-categories. The algorithm aims to preserve distances, which is a property of network design and optimization, indicating cs.NE (Networks and Economics) as a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves designing algorithms with global consistency and independent of prior queries, which is a property of information theory and security, suggesting cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as a possible sub-category.
